\" background_layout=\"light\" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth=\"off\" specialty=\"off\" background_image=\"http://centered.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2014/08/studio-garden.jpg\" transparent_background=\"off\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" inner_shadow=\"off\" parallax=\"on\" parallax_method=\"off\" module_class=\"front-image-section\"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"4_4\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\" /][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fullwidth=\"off\" specialty=\"off\" transparent_background=\"off\" background_color=\"#ffffff\" inner_shadow=\"on\" parallax=\"off\" parallax_method=\"off\" module_id=\"classes\"][et_pb_row][et_pb_column type=\"3_4\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]<h1>Classes</h1><p>Classes are taught to the standards laid out by the Iyengar Association of the UK qualification introductory levels 1 and 2.</p><p>Introductory level 1 is for newcomers to Yoga and Iyengar Yoga. Introductory level 2 is suitable for students who have some experience of Iyengar Yoga and are looking to progress in their established practise and can hold a steady head balance.</p><p>Duration of the class is 1½ hours.</p><p>Classes can be attended on a drop-in basis or block booked in advance by term. For class times see Timetable, for prices see Costs</p>[/et_pb_text][et_pb_gallery admin_label=\"Classes gallery\" gallery_ids=\"127,124,121,125,123,122,120,126\" fullwidth=\"off\" posts_number=\"8\" show_title_and_caption=\"off\" show_pagination=\"off\" background_layout=\"light\" /][/et_pb_column][et_pb_column type=\"1_4\"][et_pb_text admin_label=\"Text\" background_layout=\"light\" text_orientation=\"left\"]<ul class=\"right-nav\">\r\n<li><a href=\"/the-teacher\">The Teacher</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/preparation\">Preparation</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/timetable\">Timetable</a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"/cost\